512
00:35:27.710 --> 00:35:29.003
Helen? Helen?

513
00:35:32.007 --> 00:35:33.759
Helen. Helen.

514
00:35:38.012 --> 00:35:39.014
Hi.

515
00:35:40.389 --> 00:35:41.432
Baby.

516
00:35:48.190 --> 00:35:49.608
[shakily] Hi. baby.

517
00:35:53.653 --> 00:35:55.072
[breathing stops]

518
00:35:56.197 --> 00:35:57.365
No. no. no. no. no.

519
00:35:58.742 --> 00:36:00.909
[power lines crackling]

520
00:36:00.911 --> 00:36:02.204
[stammers]

521
00:36:07.668 --> 00:36:10.253
[grunting]

522
00:36:24.351 --> 00:36:26.561
Goddamn it. [groaning. panting]

523
00:36:26.561 --> 00:36:27.646
Okay.

524
00:36:32.025 --> 00:36:33.235
Come on. [crying]

525
00:36:36.697 --> 00:36:39.197
Somebody please help me.

526
00:36:39.199 --> 00:36:41.909
No. no. no. God. no. Don't... [sobbing]

527
00:36:41.909 --> 00:36:44.494
Please. [sniffles] Please.

528
00:36:44.496 --> 00:36:46.331
[crying]

529
00:37:07.768 --> 00:37:09.771
[crying continues]

530
00:37:14.275 --> 00:37:15.443
[crying stops]

531
00:37:17.653 --> 00:37:18.655
[gasps]

532
00:37:20.574 --> 00:37:22.576
[dramatic music playing]

533
00:37:34.880 --> 00:37:36.507
[crying]

534
00:37:37.757 --> 00:37:38.759
[exclaims]

535
00:37:56.860 --> 00:37:57.860
[whimpers]

536
00:38:17.047 --> 00:38:18.047
Hey.

537
00:38:21.175 --> 00:38:22.260
Hey.

538
00:38:30.893 --> 00:38:32.771
What... What is happening?

539
00:38:36.275 --> 00:38:37.315
[gasps]

540
00:38:37.317 --> 00:38:38.443
[shrieks]

541
00:38:40.695 --> 00:38:42.697
[panting]

542
00:38:49.288 --> 00:38:50.996
Hey! Hey! Don't you touch her!

543
00:38:50.998 --> 00:38:53.416
You put her down. Put her down.

544
00:38:53.416 --> 00:38:55.293
Get out! Go away!

545
00:38:59.755 --> 00:39:02.300
What the hell is wrong with you people?

546
00:39:03.010 --> 00:39:05.344
[crowd] We just wanna help. Carol.

547
00:39:10.684 --> 00:39:12.226
[grunting]

548
00:39:24.072 --> 00:39:26.824
[panting]

549
00:39:32.246 --> 00:39:33.748
[groans]

550
00:40:14.748 --> 00:40:17.125
What the fuck?

551
00:40:18.460 --> 00:40:20.461
[whimpering]

552
00:41:23.900 --> 00:41:25.818
[panting]

553
00:42:02.688 --> 00:42:05.317
[grunting]

554
00:42:11.239 --> 00:42:14.159
[grunting. crying]

555
00:42:15.452 --> 00:42:19.581
[grunting. panting]

556
00:42:29.215 --> 00:42:30.507
Oh. Christ. no.

557
00:42:30.509 --> 00:42:31.635
[inhales sharply]

558
00:42:32.594 --> 00:42:33.594
[groans]

559
00:42:39.141 --> 00:42:40.309
[grunts]

560
00:42:44.940 --> 00:42:48.150
[grunts. panting]

561
00:42:48.150 --> 00:42:49.568
Come on. come on. come on.

562
00:42:49.570 --> 00:42:51.445
Come on. come on. please.

563
00:42:52.989 --> 00:42:53.990
[grunts]

564
00:42:56.284 --> 00:42:57.286
[grunts]

565
00:43:00.998 --> 00:43:01.998
[grunts]

566
00:43:01.998 --> 00:43:03.708
[pants]

567
00:43:04.876 --> 00:43:05.878
[grunts]

568
00:43:06.460 --> 00:43:07.838
[children] There's a spare key.

569
00:43:08.422 --> 00:43:09.672
[exclaims]

570
00:43:10.298 --> 00:43:11.507
[both] We can show you.

571
00:43:12.009 --> 00:43:15.094
No. No. stop. Don't... Don't...
Don't... Don't come any closer.

572
00:43:15.094 --> 00:43:17.096
[neighbor boy]
We don't mean to scare you. Carol.

573
00:43:17.097 --> 00:43:18.556
You're in no danger.

574
00:43:18.556 --> 00:43:20.434
We really do want to help.

575
00:43:20.934 --> 00:43:23.476
Remember? April 2016.

576
00:43:23.478 --> 00:43:25.355
The last time you got locked out.

577
00:43:26.023 --> 00:43:28.025
You put a spare key under the flower pot.

578
00:43:29.108 --> 00:43:30.235
The one on the right.

579
00:43:31.068 --> 00:43:32.070
Back there.

580
00:43:38.869 --> 00:43:39.869
There you go.

581
00:43:42.748 --> 00:43:44.123
[panting]

582
00:43:45.833 --> 00:43:48.170
Shoo. Leave me alone.

583
00:43:49.086 --> 00:43:50.795
- Please.
- [neighbor girl] Sure. Carol.

584
00:43:50.797 --> 00:43:53.257
Just give us a couple of minutes
to clear out.

585
00:43:56.929 --> 00:43:58.846
[breathing heavily]

586
00:43:58.847 --> 00:44:00.556
[car chirps]

587
00:44:17.699 --> 00:44:19.242
[gasping]

588
00:44:31.213 --> 00:44:33.338
[crowd] We're very sorry for your loss.

589
00:44:33.340 --> 00:44:34.842
[exclaims]

590
00:44:37.552 --> 00:44:41.014
[grunting]

591
00:45:02.494 --> 00:45:04.496
[panting]

592
00:45:14.380 --> 00:45:17.384
[panting]

593
00:45:22.014 --> 00:45:23.181
[grunts]

594
00:45:27.853 --> 00:45:30.981
[car engines starting]

595
00:46:21.197 --> 00:46:22.782
[trailer door closes]

596
00:46:30.039 --> 00:46:31.458
[truck door closes]

597
00:46:53.646 --> 00:46:54.648
[mutters]

598
00:47:03.657 --> 00:47:04.907
Oh. fuck yeah!

599
00:47:04.907 --> 00:47:07.284
[groans] God bless America.

600
00:47:07.286 --> 00:47:09.913
[breathes heavily]

601
00:47:47.742 --> 00:47:51.204
[breathes deeply]

602
00:48:07.554 --> 00:48:09.597
[sips]

603
00:48:12.684 --> 00:48:13.976
[sighs]

604
00:48:17.940 --> 00:48:21.443
[sighs. breathes deeply]

605
00:48:27.782 --> 00:48:29.909
[sighs. coughs]

606
00:48:33.539 --> 00:48:36.291
[phone beeping]

607
00:48:46.760 --> 00:48:49.512
[distinguished gentleman]
<i>Hi. Carol. Thank you for calling.</i>

608
00:48:54.141 --> 00:48:55.143
Yep.

609
00:48:55.643 --> 00:48:57.936
<i>This must be so bewildering for you.</i>

610
00:48:57.938 --> 00:48:59.105
<i>So terrible.</i>

611
00:48:59.106 --> 00:49:01.775
<i>All the death and destruction
you witnessed tonight.</i>

612
00:49:02.400 --> 00:49:06.570
<i>Especially Helen's passing.
Please know none of that was intentional.</i>

613
00:49:06.572 --> 00:49:08.824
<i>You have our deepest condolences.</i>

614
00:49:09.324 --> 00:49:11.784
<i>And to say it again. you are in no danger.</i>

615
00:49:11.784 --> 00:49:13.619
<i>You are perfectly safe.</i>

616
00:49:14.663 --> 00:49:16.706
- Okay.
- <i>Your life is your own.</i>

617
00:49:17.541 --> 00:49:18.916
<i>Please know that.</i>

618
00:49:18.916 --> 00:49:21.711
<i>Your well-being
is of utmost importance to us.</i>

619
00:49:22.336 --> 00:49:23.338
O-Okay.

620
00:49:24.213 --> 00:49:25.547
<i>Completely up to you. of course.</i>

621
00:49:25.548 --> 00:49:28.800
<i>but you might want to stick close to home
for the next few days.</i>

622
00:49:28.802 --> 00:49:32.762
<i>We've a lot to clean up.
and it may be distressing for you to see.</i>

623
00:49:32.764 --> 00:49:35.599
<i>But we will put things right.</i>

624
00:49:35.601 --> 00:49:39.478
<i>To that end. if we may be of assistance
with Helen's remains--</i>

625
00:49:39.478 --> 00:49:40.938
- Nope.
- <i>Okay.</i>

626
00:49:41.606 --> 00:49:43.983
<i>If we can help you in any way
please let us know.</i>

627
00:49:43.983 --> 00:49:48.403
<i>We can deliver food. medicine.
whatever you need.</i>

628
00:49:48.405 --> 00:49:50.405
<i>Just dial zero. day or night.</i>

629
00:49:50.407 --> 00:49:54.827
<i>You will want to call from a landline
as all the cellular networks are down.</i>

630
00:49:54.827 --> 00:49:56.871
<i>But we are here for you.</i>

631
00:50:00.876 --> 00:50:03.961
<i>We feel like we're doing
all the talking here.</i>

632
00:50:05.088 --> 00:50:07.590
<i>Are there any questions
you might have for us. Carol?</i>

633
00:50:07.590 --> 00:50:08.800
<i>Anything at all.</i>

634
00:50:11.719 --> 00:50:13.137
[stammers] Uh...

635
00:50:14.306 --> 00:50:16.474
Yeah. Yeah. sure.

636
00:50:17.893 --> 00:50:19.519
I guess to start with.

637
00:50:20.353 --> 00:50:23.813
what the fuck is happening?

638
00:50:23.815 --> 00:50:25.273
<i>Well. basically--</i>

639
00:50:25.275 --> 00:50:26.775
It's an alien invasion. right?

640
00:50:26.777 --> 00:50:28.693
I mean. obviously it's an alien invasion.

641
00:50:28.695 --> 00:50:30.153
<i>Actually. no. It is not.</i>

642
00:50:30.155 --> 00:50:33.032
What the fuck it isn't. You know my name.

643
00:50:33.032 --> 00:50:35.576
You know Helen's name.

644
00:50:35.577 --> 00:50:39.248
You... You are talking to me from my TV!

645
00:50:39.831 --> 00:50:43.166
And what the fuck is with everybody's...

646
00:50:43.168 --> 00:50:44.543
Shit like this...

647
00:50:44.545 --> 00:50:48.297
And those two weird... th-the weird...
the weird neighbor kids next door.

648
00:50:48.297 --> 00:50:51.342
They know where some goddamn key... Ho-How...

649
00:50:51.342 --> 00:50:53.677
How would they know that. huh?

650
00:50:53.679 --> 00:50:57.181
- Are you reading my mind?
- <i>No. Absolutely not.</i>

651
00:50:57.181 --> 00:50:58.932
<i>We couldn't do that if we wanted to.</i>

652
00:50:58.934 --> 00:51:01.561
Who is "we?"
Why is everybody suddenly "we?"

653
00:51:01.561 --> 00:51:04.521
<i>You know. we could continue this
after you've had a good night's sleep.</i>

654
00:51:04.523 --> 00:51:06.690
Who is "we?"

655
00:51:06.692 --> 00:51:08.985
<i>"We" is us. Just us.</i>

656
00:51:08.985 --> 00:51:10.068
Who the fuck is "us?"

657
00:51:10.070 --> 00:51:12.947
<i>Us. There are no aliens.</i>

658
00:51:13.614 --> 00:51:15.074
<i>Not on this planet.</i>

659
00:51:15.074 --> 00:51:19.579
<i>We are. however. beneficiaries
of extraterrestrial technology.</i>

660
00:51:20.414 --> 00:51:23.291
<i>Fourteen months ago.
astronomers discovered a radio signal</i>

661
00:51:23.291 --> 00:51:25.668
<i>from 600 light-years away.</i>

662
00:51:26.253 --> 00:51:27.878
<i>There's no telling
how long it's been repeating.</i>

663
00:51:27.880 --> 00:51:30.590
<i>Maybe throughout all of human existence.</i>

664
00:51:31.300 --> 00:51:34.302
<i>This signal. it's made up of four tones</i>

665
00:51:34.302 --> 00:51:39.349
<i>representing guanine. uracil.
adenine and cytosine.</i>

666
00:51:40.057 --> 00:51:43.436
<i>It's a recipe. it turns out.
for a nucleotide sequence.</i>

667
00:51:44.021 --> 00:51:45.146
<i>RNA.</i>

668
00:51:46.148 --> 00:51:48.858
<i>Scientists have created
this sequence in a lab.</i>

669
00:51:48.858 --> 00:51:53.862
<i>It is not a living thing. per se.
It is more akin to a virus.</i>

670
00:51:53.864 --> 00:51:55.824
<i>Though it's not that exactly either.</i>

671
00:51:56.909 --> 00:52:01.246
<i>It's kind of a psychic glue
capable of binding us all together.</i>

672
00:52:03.164 --> 00:52:04.166
Okay.

673
00:52:05.458 --> 00:52:06.876
So. if you're not aliens...

674
00:52:08.836 --> 00:52:10.463
Who am I talking to right now?
Who are you?

675
00:52:11.340 --> 00:52:13.257
<i>This particular individual?</i>

676
00:52:13.257 --> 00:52:14.967
<i>This is Davis Taffler.</i>

677
00:52:14.967 --> 00:52:19.389
<i>Under Secretary of Agriculture
for Farm Production and Conservation.</i>

678
00:52:20.264 --> 00:52:23.934
<i>But you are currently
talking to every person on Earth.</i>

679
00:52:23.936 --> 00:52:25.771
<i>including Davis Taffler.</i>

680
00:52:26.396 --> 00:52:27.396
<i>We're all one.</i>

681
00:52:27.981 --> 00:52:29.273
How does that work?

682
00:52:30.025 --> 00:52:32.652
<i>We don't know exactly. It just does.</i>

683
00:52:33.195 --> 00:52:35.947
[exhales deeply]
Can I talk to the President?

684
00:52:35.947 --> 00:52:39.032
<i>That individual passed away this evening.
unfortunately.</i>

685
00:52:39.034 --> 00:52:43.329
<i>Along with quite a few senior members
of the United States government.</i>

686
00:52:43.329 --> 00:52:48.333
<i>Davis Taffler happened to be
nearby and intact.</i>

687
00:52:48.335 --> 00:52:49.960
<i>And he was wearing a suit. So--</i>

688
00:52:49.961 --> 00:52:52.630
So... So. you're in charge now?

689
00:52:52.630 --> 00:52:54.465
- Y... The Under Secretary of--
- <i>No.</i>

690
00:52:54.465 --> 00:52:57.510
<i>Nobody's in charge.
Or everybody's in charge.</i>

691
00:52:58.094 --> 00:52:59.887
<i>Really. there's no such thing anymore.</i>

692
00:52:59.887 --> 00:53:02.889
But-B... There's got to be others like me.

693
00:53:02.891 --> 00:53:05.309
<i>Your situation is a rare one.</i>

694
00:53:05.309 --> 00:53:08.646
<i>There appear to be
11 other individuals like yourself.</i>

695
00:53:08.646 --> 00:53:10.106
[pants] In Albuquerque?

696
00:53:10.106 --> 00:53:12.317
<i>No. In the world.</i>

697
00:53:12.818 --> 00:53:14.235
<i>We have reached out to them.</i>

698
00:53:14.735 --> 00:53:17.947
<i>Like you. they are disoriented.
Understandably.</i>

699
00:53:19.824 --> 00:53:21.367
<i>Rest assured. Carol.</i>

700
00:53:21.367 --> 00:53:24.161
<i>We will figure out
what makes you different.</i>

701
00:53:25.038 --> 00:53:26.123
Figure it out why?

702
00:53:26.789 --> 00:53:28.041
<i>So we can fix it.</i>

703
00:53:29.041 --> 00:53:30.668
<i>So you can join us.</i>

704
00:53:31.586 --> 00:53:34.088
[breathing shakily] Oh. God.

705
00:53:37.717 --> 00:53:40.304
<i>Carol. you still there?</i>

706
00:53:42.556 --> 00:53:43.556
You...

707
00:53:44.474 --> 00:53:46.474
You said my life was my own.

708
00:53:46.476 --> 00:53:49.353
<i>It is. One hundred percent.</i>

709
00:53:51.231 --> 00:53:53.275
So. what happens when I say no?

710
00:53:54.568 --> 00:54:00.032
<i>Carol. once you understand
how wonderful this is...</i>

711
00:54:01.742 --> 00:54:02.742
<i>Carol?</i>

712
00:54:04.911 --> 00:54:07.456
[breathes shakily]

713
00:54:12.460 --> 00:54:14.880
[phone ringing]

714
00:54:19.134 --> 00:54:20.217
[answering machine beeps]

715
00:54:20.219 --> 00:54:24.597
[Helen] <i>Hi! You've reached 505-796-6933.</i>

716
00:54:24.597 --> 00:54:27.307
<i>We're on the French Riviera
drinking champagne.</i>

717
00:54:27.309 --> 00:54:29.936
<i>We are not here in our sweatpants
screening your call.</i>

718
00:54:29.936 --> 00:54:32.313
- <i>Make it a good one.</i>
- [answering machine beeps]

719
00:54:32.313 --> 00:54:34.023
[Davis Taffler] <i>Carol. hello?</i>

720
00:54:34.775 --> 00:54:36.985
<i>It's us. Hello?</i>

721
00:54:38.362 --> 00:54:40.487
<i>We're sorry we upset you. Carol.</i>

722
00:54:40.489 --> 00:54:42.155
<i>We only want to make you happy.</i>

723
00:54:42.157 --> 00:54:44.451
Shut up! Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!

724
00:54:45.305 --> 00:55:45.771
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-
